article.headline: Ortega's career-high 22 leads Lady Frogs
article.linkText: No. 22 TCU tops Charlotte, wins 7 of last 8
article.story:
CHARLOTTE, N.C. (AP) -- Kim Ortega scored a career-high 22 points
Sunday to lead No. 22 TCU to a 100-91 victory over Charlotte, the
Lady Frogs' seventh win in their last eight games.

Tiffany Evans added 20 points and Ebony Shaw had 18 for TCU
(20-4, 9-2 Conference USA). Sandora Irvin finished with 12 points
and 16 rebounds while reserve Tracy Wynn had 10 points for TCU.

Andrea Daniels led Charlotte (14-10, 7-4) with 19 points. Pam
Brown and Leslie Cook each had 16 points for the 49ers, while
Monica League added 12.

Peaches Harris had 10 points to go over the 1,000-point plateau
for her career.

TCU trailed 53-51 at halftime but started the second half with a
19-8 run. The Lady Frogs were able to beat the 49ers down the court
several times for easy layups.

Ortega's 3-pointer with 3:04 left gave TCU an insurmountable
90-78 lead.

Charlotte took the lead in the first half by making 11 of 18
3-point attempts. The 49ers were just 4-for-15 from behind the
3-point arc in the second.
